HEADWORD: Juppon
<hw>Jup*pon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>jupon</ets>, fr. <ets>jupe</ets>
skirt, Sp. <ets>aljuba</ets> a Moorish garment, Ar.
<ets>jubba</ets>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written variously <asp>jupe</asp>,
<asp>jump</asp>, <asp>juppo</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A sleeveless jacket worn over the armor in the 14th
century. It fitted closely, and descended below the hips.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A petticoat.</def> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jura</ent>⟦br⟧
